<paragraph blockId="11.[174,1232,285,596]" pageId="11" pageNumber="450">
Remarks. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hering, 1938)" baseAuthorityName="Hering" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[365,696,410,437]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Terellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="450" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oasis">
<emphasis box="[365,516,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="450">Terellia oasis</emphasis>
(Hering, 1938)
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Collin, 1937)" baseAuthorityName="Collin" baseAuthorityYear="1937" box="[931,1232,410,437]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Terellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="450" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vectensis">
<emphasis box="[931,949,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="450">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[962,1062,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="450">vectensis</emphasis>
(Collin, 1937)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[241,397,442,468]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="11" pageNumber="450">Great Britain</collectingCountry>
and to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hering, 1940)" baseAuthorityName="Hering" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[490,855,442,469]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Terellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="450" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudovirens">
<emphasis box="[490,508,443,468]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="450">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[523,672,442,468]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="450">pseudovirens</emphasis>
(Hering, 1940)
</taxonomicName>
from the Near East and South-Eastern Europe, which sometimes are considered to be synonyms, differing from each other by the host plants, as well as wing and abdominal patterns, but not by the structure of male and female genitalia. Their actual taxonomic status needs additional studies involving DNA sequencing.
</paragraph>
